item.title: Star Trek: Into Darkness
item.dc:creator: robot_deodorant
item.description:
xalener:

The storyline allowed it to. And don’t fucking act like time travel and alternate universes never happen in Star Trek.
Also, every time I read this movie’s title, all I can think is “Star Trek can into space”

I know it’s allowed. It’s just bad writing.

Where the fuck are the Q? Why haven’t anyone done anything with them? If they wanted to do time travel, then have Q get bored with Picard to the point of sending a Borg cube back in time to fight Kirk/Spock.

I’m not saying it wasn’t an entertaining movie… but seeing all the different series’ as a whole, it just doesn’t fit right… but whatever.

item.dc:creator: bur
item.description:
What I meant was a ST series that moves the story forward, instead of revisiting the past. Enterprise went back, and so do these new movies. About fifteen years after Voyager would be perfect if it’s produced within the next couple of years.

Also, it didn’t turn out to be holodeck simulation. That was just a frame for the final episode that allowed actors from different series to reprise their roles.

item.title: Star Trek: Into Darkness
item.dc:creator: dky.tehkingd.u
item.description:
Looks… darker.

They’ve said repeatedly about the first movie that everything was meant to be bright and optimistic to reflect Gene Roddenberry’s view on the future (one reason why there are lots of lens flares). This… um. Looks like the opposite of that.

But that’s not necessarily a bad thing. We’ll see how it turns out.

Keresh:

Captain Kirk vs Sherlock Holmes

This. :awesome:

Soo… first Dr. Watson becomes a Hobbit, and now Holmes is trying to kill Captain Kirk. I like.[/SIZE]
